<subSubSection id="C376651AFFB1AB3D30C9FD92812CFDFF" pageId="4" pageNumber="285" type="description">
<paragraph id="8BD33691FFB1AB3D30C9FD928519FDFF" blockId="4.[156,768,523,2076]" pageId="4" pageNumber="285">
<emphasis id="B918EA83FFB1AB3D30C9FD9286A2FDBF" bold="true" box="[181,767,523,548]" pageId="4" pageNumber="285">Description based on Japanese specimen. Female</emphasis>
(n=1). Body 
<quantity id="4C949B74FFB1AB3D3155FDB58528FDDF" box="[297,373,556,580]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="6.3" pageId="4" pageNumber="285" unit="mm" value="6.3">6.3 mm</quantity>
, slender, mat and inpunctate, covered with silver setae.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BD33691FFB1AB3D30C9FDF4862FFC70" blockId="4.[156,768,523,2076]" pageId="4" pageNumber="285">
Head 0.6×as long as wide. Area combined clypeus with face wide (
<figureCitation id="13572A14FFB1AB3D3170FD17850AFD3D" box="[268,343,654,678]" captionStart="Figs 12–27" captionStartId="2.[156,193,1135,1157]" captionTargetBox="[415,1171,206,1095]" captionTargetId="figure-530@2.[414,1173,205,1097]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="Figs 12–27. Japanese species of Pyracmon, P. monticola sp. nov. (12–18, holotype, KPM-NK 74578), P. nigrifemur Barron and Walley, 1983 (19–23, KPM-NK 74575) and P. sepiellus (Holmgren, 1860) (24–27, NIAES), females from Japan—12, 13, 19, 24, head, frontal (12, 19, 24) and dorsal (13) view; 14, 20, right (14) and left (20) mandible, frontal view; 15, 21, 25, apical margin of clypeus, frontal view; 16, 22, 26, propodeum, dorsal view, rugae on right half omitted; 17, 23, 27, T I and basal part of T II, lateral view; 18, apex of ovipositor, lateral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5738273" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5738273/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="285">Fig. 24</figureCitation>
), 0.8×as long as wide, slightly convex in lateral view. Apical margin of clypeus blunt, simply arched, without margined areas and a median smooth convexity (
<figureCitation id="13572A14FFB1AB3D30DFFD7684ACFC9C" box="[163,241,751,775]" captionStart="Figs 12–27" captionStartId="2.[156,193,1135,1157]" captionTargetBox="[415,1171,206,1095]" captionTargetId="figure-530@2.[414,1173,205,1097]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="Figs 12–27. Japanese species of Pyracmon, P. monticola sp. nov. (12–18, holotype, KPM-NK 74578), P. nigrifemur Barron and Walley, 1983 (19–23, KPM-NK 74575) and P. sepiellus (Holmgren, 1860) (24–27, NIAES), females from Japan—12, 13, 19, 24, head, frontal (12, 19, 24) and dorsal (13) view; 14, 20, right (14) and left (20) mandible, frontal view; 15, 21, 25, apical margin of clypeus, frontal view; 16, 22, 26, propodeum, dorsal view, rugae on right half omitted; 17, 23, 27, T I and basal part of T II, lateral view; 18, apex of ovipositor, lateral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5738273" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5738273/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="285">Fig. 25</figureCitation>
). Gena broadly rounded in dorsal view, distinctly receding. Malar space 0.75×as long as basal mandibular width. Lower part of occipital carina joined with hypostomal carina. Mandible narrow, slightly tapering distally, lower margin with narrow lamella. POL 1.4×as long as OD. OOL 1.5×as long as OD. Antenna with 27 (
<quantity id="4C949B74FFB1AB3D320AFC0B86F3FC31" box="[630,686,914,938]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="7.366" pageId="4" pageNumber="285" unit="in" value="29.0">29 in</quantity>
<bibRefCitation id="EFFD4B60FFB1AB3D32C4FC0B851AFC50" author="Barron, J. R. &amp; Walley, G. S." pageId="4" pageNumber="285" pagination="227 - 241" refId="ref4315" refString="Barron, J. R. and Walley, G. S. 1983. Revision of the Holarctic genus Pyracmon (Hymenoptera: Ichneumonidae). Canadian Entomologist 115: 227 - 241." type="journal article" year="1983">Barron and Walley 1983</bibRefCitation>
) flagellomeres. Length of FL I 4.5×as long as maximum depth. FL I: II: III=2.0: 1.55:1.5.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BD33691FFB1AB3D30C9FC6D85CDF90D" blockId="4.[156,768,523,2076]" pageId="4" pageNumber="285">
Mesosoma. Pronotum covered with longitudinal striae on ventral 0.6 (
<figureCitation id="13572A14FFB1AB3D3167FB8D853BFBB7" box="[283,358,1044,1068]" captionStart="Figs 1–11" captionStartId="1.[156,193,1471,1493]" captionTargetBox="[189,1398,207,1430]" captionTargetId="figure-240@1.[187,1400,205,1432]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="Figs 1–11. Japanese species of Pyracmon, P. monticola sp. nov. (1–5, holotype, KPM-NK 74578), P. nigrifemur Barron and Walley, 1983 (6–8, KPM-NK 74575) and P. sepiellus (Holmgren, 1860) (9–11, NIAES), females from Japan—1, 6, 9, lateral habitus; 2, 7, 10, mesosoma, lateral view; 3, 8, 11, propodeum, dorsal view; 4, right fore wing; 5, right hind wing." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5738269" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5738269/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="285">Fig. 10</figureCitation>
). Epomia absent. Notauli absent. Epicnemial carina complete, its dorsal end joined with anterior margin of mesopleuron. Mesopleuron with a large smooth area on speculum and with a longitudinal rugulose area between epicnemial carina and speculum. Propodeal carinae strong and complete, as in 
<figureCitation id="13572A14FFB1AB3D31CEFB2E85A0FB54" box="[434,509,1207,1231]" captionStart="Figs 1–11" captionStartId="1.[156,193,1471,1493]" captionTargetBox="[189,1398,207,1430]" captionTargetId="figure-240@1.[187,1400,205,1432]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="Figs 1–11. Japanese species of Pyracmon, P. monticola sp. nov. (1–5, holotype, KPM-NK 74578), P. nigrifemur Barron and Walley, 1983 (6–8, KPM-NK 74575) and P. sepiellus (Holmgren, 1860) (9–11, NIAES), females from Japan—1, 6, 9, lateral habitus; 2, 7, 10, mesosoma, lateral view; 3, 8, 11, propodeum, dorsal view; 4, right fore wing; 5, right hind wing." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5738269" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5738269/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="285">Figs 11</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="13572A14FFB1AB3D3274FB2E867EFB54" box="[520,547,1207,1231]" captionStart="Figs 12–27" captionStartId="2.[156,193,1135,1157]" captionTargetBox="[415,1171,206,1095]" captionTargetId="figure-530@2.[414,1173,205,1097]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="Figs 12–27. Japanese species of Pyracmon, P. monticola sp. nov. (12–18, holotype, KPM-NK 74578), P. nigrifemur Barron and Walley, 1983 (19–23, KPM-NK 74575) and P. sepiellus (Holmgren, 1860) (24–27, NIAES), females from Japan—12, 13, 19, 24, head, frontal (12, 19, 24) and dorsal (13) view; 14, 20, right (14) and left (20) mandible, frontal view; 15, 21, 25, apical margin of clypeus, frontal view; 16, 22, 26, propodeum, dorsal view, rugae on right half omitted; 17, 23, 27, T I and basal part of T II, lateral view; 18, apex of ovipositor, lateral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5738273" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5738273/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="285">26</figureCitation>
. Lateromedian longitudinal carina and lateral longitudinal carina complete. Area petiolaris with some transverse rugae (
<figureCitation id="13572A14FFB1AB3D3242FB6186D2FA8B" box="[574,655,1272,1296]" captionStart="Figs 1–11" captionStartId="1.[156,193,1471,1493]" captionTargetBox="[189,1398,207,1430]" captionTargetId="figure-240@1.[187,1400,205,1432]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="Figs 1–11. Japanese species of Pyracmon, P. monticola sp. nov. (1–5, holotype, KPM-NK 74578), P. nigrifemur Barron and Walley, 1983 (6–8, KPM-NK 74575) and P. sepiellus (Holmgren, 1860) (9–11, NIAES), females from Japan—1, 6, 9, lateral habitus; 2, 7, 10, mesosoma, lateral view; 3, 8, 11, propodeum, dorsal view; 4, right fore wing; 5, right hind wing." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5738269" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5738269/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="285">Figs 11</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="13572A14FFB1AB3D32E3FB6186E6FA8B" box="[671,699,1272,1296]" captionStart="Figs 12–27" captionStartId="2.[156,193,1135,1157]" captionTargetBox="[415,1171,206,1095]" captionTargetId="figure-530@2.[414,1173,205,1097]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="Figs 12–27. Japanese species of Pyracmon, P. monticola sp. nov. (12–18, holotype, KPM-NK 74578), P. nigrifemur Barron and Walley, 1983 (19–23, KPM-NK 74575) and P. sepiellus (Holmgren, 1860) (24–27, NIAES), females from Japan—12, 13, 19, 24, head, frontal (12, 19, 24) and dorsal (13) view; 14, 20, right (14) and left (20) mandible, frontal view; 15, 21, 25, apical margin of clypeus, frontal view; 16, 22, 26, propodeum, dorsal view, rugae on right half omitted; 17, 23, 27, T I and basal part of T II, lateral view; 18, apex of ovipositor, lateral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5738273" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5738273/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="285">26</figureCitation>
). Fore wing length 5.0 mm (
<quantity id="4C949B74FFB1AB3D3107FA81859AFAAB" box="[379,455,1304,1328]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.7" pageId="4" pageNumber="285" unit="mm" value="4.7">4.7 mm</quantity>
in 
<bibRefCitation id="EFFD4B60FFB1AB3D3192FA8086A8FAAB" author="Barron, J. R. &amp; Walley, G. S." box="[494,757,1304,1328]" pageId="4" pageNumber="285" pagination="227 - 241" refId="ref4315" refString="Barron, J. R. and Walley, G. S. 1983. Revision of the Holarctic genus Pyracmon (Hymenoptera: Ichneumonidae). Canadian Entomologist 115: 227 - 241." type="journal article" year="1983">Barron and Walley, 1983</bibRefCitation>
). Postero-distal corner of second discoidal cell in form of an acute to right angle (85°). Areolet sessile, receiving second recurrent vein little distad of the middle. Hind wing with discoidella, slightly pigmented basally, clearly recognizable by light reflection. Hind femur 5.1×as long as maximum depth in lateral view. Hind tibia covered with minute (normal) setae, its dorsal surface with some short bristles. Longest spur of hind tibia shorter than half length of first tarsomere. TS I without a continuous, straight, median ventral row if very closely spaced small setae. TS I: II: III: VI: V=4.4: 2.0: 1.3: 0.8: 1.1.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BD33691FFB1AB3D30C9F90686E6F883" blockId="4.[156,768,523,2076]" pageId="4" pageNumber="285">
Metasoma. T I 2.6×as long as maximum width, its base smooth. T I in profile dorsally without an obtuse angulation (
<figureCitation id="13572A14FFB1AB3D30DFF97984B3F963" box="[163,238,1760,1784]" captionStart="Figs 12–27" captionStartId="2.[156,193,1135,1157]" captionTargetBox="[415,1171,206,1095]" captionTargetId="figure-530@2.[414,1173,205,1097]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="Figs 12–27. Japanese species of Pyracmon, P. monticola sp. nov. (12–18, holotype, KPM-NK 74578), P. nigrifemur Barron and Walley, 1983 (19–23, KPM-NK 74575) and P. sepiellus (Holmgren, 1860) (24–27, NIAES), females from Japan—12, 13, 19, 24, head, frontal (12, 19, 24) and dorsal (13) view; 14, 20, right (14) and left (20) mandible, frontal view; 15, 21, 25, apical margin of clypeus, frontal view; 16, 22, 26, propodeum, dorsal view, rugae on right half omitted; 17, 23, 27, T I and basal part of T II, lateral view; 18, apex of ovipositor, lateral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5738273" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5738273/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="285">Fig. 27</figureCitation>
). Subapical part of lower valve of ovipositor slightly widened. Ovipositor sheath 1.0×as long as hind tibia.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BD33691FFB1AB3D30C9F8B88169FEFB" blockId="4.[156,768,523,2076]" lastBlockId="4.[821,1432,198,970]" pageId="4" pageNumber="285">
Coloration (
<figureCitation id="13572A14FFB1AB3D314EF8B885C6F8A2" box="[306,411,1825,1849]" captionStart="Figs 1–11" captionStartId="1.[156,193,1471,1493]" captionTargetBox="[189,1398,207,1430]" captionTargetId="figure-240@1.[187,1400,205,1432]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="Figs 1–11. Japanese species of Pyracmon, P. monticola sp. nov. (1–5, holotype, KPM-NK 74578), P. nigrifemur Barron and Walley, 1983 (6–8, KPM-NK 74575) and P. sepiellus (Holmgren, 1860) (9–11, NIAES), females from Japan—1, 6, 9, lateral habitus; 2, 7, 10, mesosoma, lateral view; 3, 8, 11, propodeum, dorsal view; 4, right fore wing; 5, right hind wing." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5738269" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5738269/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="285">Figs 9–11</figureCitation>
). Body (excluding wings and legs) black to blackish brown, except for: mandible except apex, palpi and membranous part of metasomal sternites yellow; tegula, posterior margins of metasomal tergites and ovipositor yellowish brown. Wings hyaline. Veins and pterostigma blackish brown to brown except for yellowish brown wing base. Fore and mid legs reddish brown to yellowish brown except for largely black coxae. Hind leg blackish brown to black except for: trochantellus reddish brown; base and apex of femur narrowly tinged with reddish brown; tibia except for black apical part and tibial spurs reddish brown (base of tibia slightly and narrowly darkened); base of each tarsal segment more or less tinged with yellowish brown.
</paragraph>
