<subSubSection id="C376651AFFB1AB3D3332FC898097FC51" pageId="4" pageNumber="285" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8BD33691FFB1AB3D3332FC898097FC51" blockId="4.[821,1432,198,970]" pageId="4" pageNumber="285">
<emphasis id="B918EA83FFB1AB3D3332FC8987EFFCB3" bold="true" box="[846,946,784,808]" pageId="4" pageNumber="285">Remarks.</emphasis>
This is the first record of this species from 
<collectingCountry id="F37B7601FFB1AB3D3349FCA8872DFCD3" box="[821,880,817,840]" name="Japan" pageId="4" pageNumber="285">Japan</collectingCountry>
. The coloration of hind femur with intraspecific variation (
<bibRefCitation id="EFFD4B60FFB1AB3D3311FCC8802DFCF2" author="Barron, J. R. &amp; Walley, G. S." box="[877,1136,849,873]" pageId="4" pageNumber="285" pagination="227 - 241" refId="ref4315" refString="Barron, J. R. and Walley, G. S. 1983. Revision of the Holarctic genus Pyracmon (Hymenoptera: Ichneumonidae). Canadian Entomologist 115: 227 - 241." type="journal article" year="1983">Barron and Walley, 1983</bibRefCitation>
), 
<emphasis id="B918EA83FFB1AB3D34F8FCC880FCFCF3" box="[1156,1185,849,872]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="285">i.e.</emphasis>
, specimens of northern distribution mostly dark, of southern mostly pale. The Japanese materials collected in the northern area of 
<collectingCountry id="F37B7601FFB1AB3D3561FC0B8105FC32" box="[1309,1368,914,937]" name="Japan" pageId="4" pageNumber="285">Japan</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingRegion id="49A8F873FFB1AB3D351EFC0B8732FC51" country="Japan" name="Hokkaido" pageId="4" pageNumber="285">Hokkaido</collectingRegion>
, and well accord with this pattern.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
